value.0: A protector of Winya Ravana, these elves were called from Evermeet itself.

As with many exquisitely-crafted bows, many attribute these to the elves, especially as the first examples of their kind started to appear in the hands in the upper ranks of Winyan soldiers. Yet, the few elven scholars fortunate enough to closely examine these bows argue that they have no origin of elvenkind at all - rather than to precisely pierce their target, these weapons are built for a more brutal purpose. Instead of focusing on aim and precision, these bows focus on speed, fast enough that the wind currents left in the wake of arrows fired are a danger in themselves, ripping at the target in a vicious manner akin to a flying saw. Such violent methods are rarely found in elven crafts, leaving the origins of these weapons much a mystery.

This shield is commonly mass produced during times of war to protect valuable field officers. Sometimes they gather in merchants inventories during periods of peace or when a surplus has been made. They are definitely more practical than elaborate, a fairly straight-forward protection.

Dogma of Aerdrie faenya:   The ever-changing reaches of the sky are the great gift of the Winged Mother. Take flight into her windswept embrace, and gambol amid the clouds. Honor those who dwell with the Aerdrie and cherish the birds dancing on her tresses Change is beautiful and chaos births new life. Ascend, soar, glide, dive, and ascend again and relish in the freedom that the Winged Mother bequeaths.
